			<ns0:name>mcgra...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/100177598732114324016/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">As an ABI compatibility issue, we need to preserve the old behavior (at least for the old IRT query string) forever regardless, of course.

My analysis of the nacl-glibc source code indicates that in fact PT_GNU_STACK on the main nexe is ignored (because the phdrs are not in the address space), so it defaults to the old (Linux) compatibility mode which is to presume executable stack is required.  But that is not consistent with what we see in the simple pthread tests under --nacl_glibc.  So more investigation is required to understand what is going on, and that investigation is not a high priority for me.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-04-23T18:18:36.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-04-23T18:18:36.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 8 by mcgra...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3402#c8" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3402/comments/full/8" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>